
Overview of noun pity

The noun pity has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (6) commiseration, pity, ruth, pathos -- (a feeling of sympathy and sorrow for the misfortunes of others; "the blind are too often objects of pity")
2. (3) pity, shame -- (an unfortunate development; "it's a pity he couldn't do it")
3. compassion, pity -- (the humane quality of understanding the suffering of others and wanting to do something about it)

